{"article_id":"n9wBAWMWmIo1wK2s","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON ( ) -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The drive","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to expand vote-by-mail options during the coronavirus pandemic","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"has emerged as the centerpiece of a growing political fight ahead of November ' s election .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"President Donald Trump and his Republican allies have attacked the idea","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"of expanding mail balloting ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"arguing","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"it is vulnerable to fraud","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"and openly worrying","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"that easier voting would hurt their party ' s chances in November .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Democrats and voting rights groups say","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"it is a way","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"to protect voters from the deadly virus ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"and that a failure","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"to guarantee that option amid a pandemic","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"will disenfranchise millions of Americans , especially the poor and African Americans","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"who are deemed more vulnerable to the virus","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"and who tend to vote Democratic .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Last week ' s turbulent Wisconsin elections ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"which went ahead","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"after Republicans blocked Democratic efforts","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"to delay in-person voting","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"and expand absentee balloting ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"illustrated the partisan divide","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"- and the mounting urgency","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"to find a solution before the Nov. 3 U.S. election .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Republicans say","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"voting by mail is more susceptible to fraud","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"since voters do not have to appear in person at a polling place .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"\" Mail ballots are a very dangerous thing for this country","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"because they ' re cheaters .","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"They go","depth":16},{"id":32,"text":"and collect them .","depth":16},{"id":33,"text":"They ' re fraudulent in many cases , \"","depth":15},{"id":34,"text":"Trump told a recent coronavirus briefing ,","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"without providing evidence .","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"He acknowledged","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"he cast an absentee ballot by mail last month in Florida ' s Republican primary .","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"But Trump also voiced what Democrats believe","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"is the prime motivation","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"for opposing vote by mail :","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"It will lead to a higher turnout","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"that hurts Republican candidates .","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"Trump told Fox News","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"a shift","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"to making voting easier","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"would mean \" you ' d never have a Republican elected in this country again . \"","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"Trevor Potter , a Republican former chairman of the Federal Election Commission","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"who founded the Washington-based Campaign Legal Center ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Trump ' s reaction was puzzling","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"since Republicans often do well in mail-in balloting .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"\" Polls show","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"older Americans , those","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"thought to be most vulnerable to the virus ,","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"are more likely to support President Trump than other voters , \"","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"Potter said ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"conservative","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"Utah is one of five states","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"that has gone to all-mail voting with little sign of fraud .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"A series of academic , government and news investigations over the years have found little evidence of election fraud of any kind .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"Utah and four other states","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"that vote entirely by mail","depth":15},{"id":64,"text":"- Hawaii , Oregon , Washington and Colorado -","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"have reported little fraud .","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"Trump ,","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"who has often said without evidence","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"that millions voted illegally in 2016 ,","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"formed a commission after the campaign","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"to investigate .","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"It disbanded in January 2018","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"without finding any evidence","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"to back up his allegations .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"Election experts say","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"there have been scattered incidents of people","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"collecting and manipulating absentee ballots in a process","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"known as \" ballot harvesting . \"","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"The most recent example came in a 2018 North Carolina congressional race ,","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"the outcome of which was overturned","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"when it was determined","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"an operative gathered ballots for the Republican candidate .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"More than a dozen states already have postponed primaries or expanded vote by mail","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"to avoid forcing residents to go to crowded polling places .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"Vote by mail is hardly a novelty .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"A report by the U.S. Election Assistance Commission says","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"the process was used by about one-quarter of all voters in the 2018 midterm elections .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"Along with the five states","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"that vote entirely by mail ,","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"28 states will allow voters to request a mail ballot","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"without any excuse in November ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"according to the Brennan Center for Justice .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"\" We are not reinventing the wheel here .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"This is upscaling what is already taking place , \"","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"U.S . Senator Ron Wyden , co-sponsor with fellow Democratic Senator Amy Klobuchar of a bill","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"to expand vote by mail and early voting to all states ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"told reporters last week .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"There are still 17 states such as Texas , New York and Louisiana","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"that would need to change their policies","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"to guarantee","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"that everyone","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"who wants to vote by mail in November","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"can ,","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"the Brennan Center said .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"It will be expensive .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"The Brennan Center estimated","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"the cost","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"of ensuring","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"that vote by mail was available for all voters","depth":15},{"id":109,"text":"could be up to $ 1.4 billion ,","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"with postage alone costing up to $ 600 million .","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"Even advocates of vote by mail say","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"states would need to keep the option of in-person voting , for voters with disabilities , those","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"who need language access assistance","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"or do not have regular mail access .","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"Democratic and Republican-aligned groups across the country are already fighting in federal and state courts over whether and how to expand access to mail-in voting .","depth":3},{"id":116,"text":"On March 30 , 27 New Mexico county clerks petitioned the state Supreme Court to conduct their June 2 primary almost entirely by mail","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"and allow all voters to be mailed an absentee ballot .","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"State Republicans sued","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"to oppose both changes .","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"In Texas , the Democratic Party sued the state ' s Republican leadership in federal court on April 7","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"to allow no-excuse absentee voting .","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"Texas law requires voters to provide an excuse , such as disability ,","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"when requesting an absentee ballot .","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"In Georgia , the American Civil Liberties Union sued the Republican secretary of state last Wednesday in federal court","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"for requiring voters to pay their own postage","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"when submitting mail-in absentee ballots and applications ,","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"arguing","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"that was tantamount to a poll tax .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":257,"left":0,"right":256,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":256,"left":242,"right":255,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":145,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":131,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":130,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":130,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":136,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":132,"right":135,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclear